.TH FEED 1 "March 2026" "feed" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
feed \- terminal based prompter for AI API services
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B feed
[\fB--debug\fR | \fB-d\fR] "\fIyour prompt here\fR"
.SH DESCRIPTION
feed is a command line tool that sends prompts to AI services using the OpenAI REST protocol. It is designed to work with APIs like xAI Grok and OpenAI. The tool takes a prompt, sends it to the configured AI model, and prints the formatted response.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --debug, -d
Enable debug mode. Prints the API URL, JSON payload, and raw response from the API.
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
The following environment variables must be set:
.TP
.B FEED_URL
The URL of the AI API endpoint.
.TP
.B FEED_KEY
The API key for authentication.
.TP
.B FEED_MODEL
The model name to use (e.g., grok-1).
.PP
Optional variables:
.TP
.B FEED_USER
Name to use in prompts. Defaults to "Anonymous" if unset.
.TP
.B FEED_CONTEXT
Context/system prompt for the AI. Defaults to "You are Grok, a helpful and maximally truthful AI built by xAI." if unset.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
feed "What is the capital of France?"
Send a simple prompt to the AI.
.TP
feed --debug "Explain quantum physics"
Send a prompt with debug output enabled.
.TP
feed "$(cat README.md)"
Include file contents in the prompt.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
Requires curl utility, which is available in most Linux distributions.
.SH SEE ALSO
curl(1)
.SH AUTHOR
feed is developed as an open source project.